verbose_text: CAPS is caused by abnormalities in the NLRP3 protein in which a genetic mutation in the NACHT domain causes continuous overproduction of interleukin (IL)-1beta, resulting in chronic inflammation and progressive tissue damage 4, 5, 6, 7.
